com.github.arachnidium.model.common

Class FunctionalPart<S extends Handle>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.arachnidium.model.abstractions.ModelObject<S>
      • com.github.arachnidium.model.common.FunctionalPart<S>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDestroyable, ISwitchesToItself, ITakesPictureOfItSelf, IDecomposable, org.openqa.selenium.internal.WrapsDriver
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BrowserPage, NativeContent, WebViewContent

    public abstract class FunctionalPart<S extends Handle>
extends ModelObject<S>
implements ITakesPictureOfItSelf, ISwitchesToItself
    This class is for description of browser or mobile UI or the fragment of this UI. It is assumed that this description can be reusable. Interaction and behavior should describe subclasses of this.

      • getPart

        public <T extends IDecomposable> T getPart(Class<T> partClass)
        This method returns another UI description (child). It is assumed that current UI is more generalized and the child is more specific.

        It means, that required UI or fragment of UI is on the same browser window/mobile screen as the current. Also "child" is inside the same frame as the current (it is actual for browser and mobile hybrid apps).

      • getPart

        public <T extends IDecomposable> T getPart(Class<T> partClass,
                                           HowToGetByFrames path,
                                           org.openqa.selenium.By by)
        This method returns another UI description (child). It is assumed that current UI is more generalized and the child is more specific.

        It means, that required UI or fragment of UI is on the same browser window/mobile screen as the current. Also "child" is inside the same frame as the current (it is actual for browser and mobile hybrid apps).


        The required piece of UI is inside frame (it is actual for browser and mobile hybrid apps). Path to desired frame is specified by HowToGetByFrames instance.

        The root WebElement where UI is placed is known. The given By defines the locator strategy of the searching for the root element.
        Specified by:
        getPart in interface IDecomposable
        Specified by:
        getPart in class ModelObject<S extends Handle>
        Parameters:
        partClass - is required class that implements IDecomposable
        path - is a path to frame which is specified by HowToGetByFrames
        by - Is a locator strategy which is used to get the root WebElement
        Returns:
        The instance of required class specified by @param partClass
        See Also:
        ModelObject.getPart(Class, HowToGetByFrames), IDecomposable.getPart(Class, HowToGetByFrames), HowToGetByFrames
